name: date_diff
description:
Subtracts the `startTimestamp` from the `endTimestamp` and returns the difference in multiples of `unit`.
If `startTimestamp` is later than the `endTimestamp`, negative values are returned.

params.name: startTimestamp
params.description: A string representing a start timestamp

params.name: endTimestamp
params.description: A string representing an end timestamp

params.name: startTimestamp
params.description: A string representing a start timestamp

params.name: endTimestamp
params.description: A string representing an end timestamp

examples:
ROW date1 = TO_DATETIME("2023-12-02T11:00:00.000Z"), date2 = TO_DATETIME("2023-12-02T11:00:00.001Z")
| EVAL dd_ms = DATE_DIFF("microseconds", date1, date2)
